[SN]TITLE[SN]
Manon Carpenter: Wales' ex-world champion signs for new team

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Welsh downhill mountain bike rider Manon Carpenter has joined German team Radon ahead of the 2017 race season.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 2014 World Champion, who has signed a two-year contract, left Madison Saracen after six years in 2016.
Carpenter, 23, is back in training after her season came to an end when she broke a collarbone in a crash at the World Championships in Val di Sole.
The 2017 Downhill World Cup will get underway in Lourdes, France on April 29-30.
